This is the original string from {{JiraWebActionSupport.properties}}:
{code:java}
wiki.renderer.help.misc.escape=Escape special character X (i.e. '{)
{code}
Note that there is a single-quote character before the left curly brace. This is important because these strings get evaluated by the Java {{MessageFormat}} class, and that single-quote escapes the curly-brace. If you don't include the single-quote, then the {{MessageFormat}} class will throw an exception instead, and the message will fail to display. For example, in the Polish translation file {{jira_cloud_i18n_pl_PL.properties}} we have this:
{code:java}
wiki.renderer.help.misc.escape=Przed znakami specjalnymi wstawiaj symbol modyfikacji (tzn. {)
{code}
That results in the exception reported in
 * [https://getsupport.atlassian.com/browse/PCS-16073]
 * [https://getsupport.atlassian.com/browse/JST-600647] - German
 * https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-75093

The translations *must* preserve the {{'}} character to prevent this. I've tagged the languages where I found that it has been dropped.
